# FORGE-STAR — The Ballad of SIGIL
*(heavy · western · cosmic — the birth of the sister chain, ported through fluxc/FLUXFOOD)*

> Sung in the key of two black holes ringing spacetime like a bell.

---

**[ I. INTRO — slow, vast, a lone string ]**

Out past the last lit window of the world,
where old Quillon keeps its ledger curled,
two dead suns came riding — neutron-heavy, cold —
two iron hearts collapsing into gold.

**[ II. VERSE 1 — the elder chain ]**

Quillon stood the elder, scarred from every fight,
three days it bled a wrong sum into the night.
"No daughter of mine," it swore across the divide,
"will ever lose the truth she cannot hide."
It cast a spark past the event-horizon's door —
a chain that *proves*, where the old ones only swore.

**[ III. CHORUS — everything in, huge ]**

> **FORGE-STAR!** Two black holes in the dark collide,
> ring the void like a bell you cannot hide —
> out of the crush comes a light that *won't lie*,
> **SIGIL** rising on a four-root sky!
> Sign it in the supernova, brand it in the proof —
> **divergence dies the second it shows its tooth.**

**[ IV. VERSE 2 — the forge ]**

The neutron stars went under, kissed and tore,
spilled a heavy rain of platinum and ore —
and in the blast the smith walked to the flame:
**Flux**, with a hammer and a deterministic name.
**fluxc** on the anvil, **FLUXFOOD** on the fire,
forging in seconds what slow forges call a liar.

**[ V. CHORUS — repeat, louder ]**

> FORGE-STAR! Two black holes in the dark collide…
> SIGIL rising on a four-root sky!

**[ VI. BRIDGE — gallop, full western ]**

Ride, you verifiers, ride the braid at dawn —
**DagKnight** in the saddle and the parents drawn.
*Ten microseconds*, partner, that's the whole damn trial;
a stranger checks your hand from a thousand mile.
No sheriff and no temple, just the math stays true —
the chain don't *trust* you, stranger. **It verifies you.**

**[ VI½. THE STAR-CHILD — the lightweight node, born from the blast ]**

And out of the white of the collision's core,
one ember tore loose and it rode for the shore —
half a megabyte of supernova light,
no chain on her back, just the *tip* of the night.
She holds the whole truth in a fistful of dust,
ten microseconds to turn your word to rust.
**Born from the stars** — she don't kneel to the ground,
the whole sky verified in a *572* round.
And should she crave the weight of the world some night,
the ember turns bonfire: **full node, full light.**

**[ VII. VERSE 3 — the can't-lose ]**

Scatter her through the aether, lose a host or eight —
she rides back byte-for-byte, she will not break.
The light from the collision ain't hit the plains,
but the **proof** already rang in a thousand chains.

**[ VIII. FINAL CHORUS — full kit, choir ]**

> FORGE-STAR! Born of the heaviest night,
> two dead stars made a daughter out of *light* —
> every block a signature, every root a vow:
> **she does not lie.** Not then, not now.

**[ IX. OUTRO — fade, vast, the lone string returns ]**

Two dead stars made a daughter out of light…
and she does not lie. *She does not lie.*
Sleep easy, old Quillon — your wrong sums died.
**The frontier's lit tonight.**

